# Olim App — environment variables.
#
# Variable names below match what the Vercel ↔ Supabase integration provisions,
# so the same names work locally and on Vercel.
#
# --- Environment file layout (local-first dev) -----------------------------
# Next.js loads env files with `.env.$(NODE_ENV).local` winning over `.env.local`.
# We use that precedence so `pnpm dev` / local `pnpm build` are LOCAL-FIRST while
# `.env.local` keeps the prod remote for explicit prod-facing work:
#
#   .env.development.local   → local Supabase stack (127.0.0.1:54321). Used by
#                              `pnpm dev`. Overrides .env.local. Gitignored.
#   .env.production.local    → local stack too, so a local `pnpm build && pnpm
#                              start` also talks to the local DB. Gitignored.
#   .env.local               → the SHARED prod remote + real secrets (service
#                              role, Resend, revalidate). Used for prod-facing
#                              tooling and as the base when no *.local override
#                              applies. Gitignored — never commit secrets.
#
# Vercel has none of these *.local files — it uses its own project env, so this
# split never affects deploys. Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill it in; for
# LOCAL dev use the values printed by `supabase start` (see "Local dev defaults"
# at the bottom — Supabase's well-known local keys, safe only on localhost).

# --- Supabase: client (browser-safe) ---------------------------------------
# Provisioned by the Vercel integration. The publishable key is the new-style
# client key; the anon JWT is its legacy equivalent (either works with the JS SDK).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="https://<project-ref>.supabase.co"
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="sb_publishable_..."

# Legacy anon JWT (alternative to the publishable key above — either works).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY="<anon-jwt>"

# --- Analytics + errors (Phase 4; optional, env-gated) ---------------------
# When absent, PostHog and Sentry are silently disabled (local/CI). Set in
# Vercel (prod) to enable. Create free projects: posthog.com, sentry.io.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY="phc_..."
# NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST="https://us.i.posthog.com"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN="https://...@...ingest.sentry.io/..."

# --- Supabase: server-only (NEVER expose to the browser) -------------------
# The content import (`pnpm content:import`) writes with the service-role key,
# which bypasses RLS. Keep it server-side only.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="<service-role-jwt>"
# New-style secret key equivalent (either the service-role JWT above or this works).
SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY="sb_secret_..."

# Optional: direct Postgres connection (provisioned by the integration; used by
# tooling, not the app runtime). Pooled + non-pooled variants.
# POSTGRES_URL="postgres://..."
# POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING="postgres://..."

# --- Deadline reminders (Phase 7b; server / Edge Function only) -------------
# Resend sends the reminder emails. Create a free account at resend.com and put
# the API key here (and as a Supabase secret for the deployed Edge Function:
# `supabase secrets set RESEND_API_KEY=...`). Absent → the reminder function
# computes but does not send (dry-run), so local tests never hit the network.
# RESEND_API_KEY="re_..."
# The verified/onboarding sender the reminder emails come from.
# REMINDER_FROM_EMAIL="Olim App <onboarding@resend.dev>"
# Secret that signs one-click unsubscribe links (HMAC). Any long random string.
# REMINDER_UNSUBSCRIBE_SECRET="<long-random-string>"

# --- AI search (Phase 8; server-only, env-gated) ---------------------------
# Gemini powers both the retrieval embeddings and the grounded answer. Absent →
# the "Спроси об Израиле" box degrades to "AI-ответы скоро" and keyword search
# still works (CI/preview/local без ключа не падают). NEVER expose to the browser
# (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix — the LLM client stays server-side). Create a free key at
# aistudio.google.com. Set it as a Vercel env var (prod) and a Supabase secret if
# ever called from an Edge Function.
# GEMINI_API_KEY="AIza..."
# Optional overrides: OLIM_ANSWER_MODEL (default gemini-3.1-flash-lite),
# OLIM_ASK_RATE_PER_IP (5), OLIM_ASK_RATE_GLOBAL (12) — the global RPM ceiling that
# protects the free Gemini quota.

# For the CI eval gate (pnpm eval), point these at a DB seeded with embeddings:
# EVAL_SUPABASE_URL / EVAL_SUPABASE_KEY are read as NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* in CI.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local dev defaults (from `supabase start` — localhost only, not secret)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL="http://127.0.0.1:54321"
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="sb_publishable_ACJWlzQHlZjBrEguHvfOxg_3BJgxAaH"
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY="<SERVICE_ROLE_KEY printed by `supabase start`>"
#
# Re-print these any time with:  supabase status
